<body>

    <h1>Project Design Report (PDR)</h1>
    <h3 style="text-align:center;">Medication Reminder Mobile Application</h3>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Medication non-adherence is a common problem affecting many people, especially
            those taking multiple medicines or managing chronic illnesses. Forgetting to
            take medicine at the right time can lead to health complications.
        </p>
        <p>
            This project focuses on developing a medication reminder mobile application
            that helps users remember when and which medicine to take using scheduled
            reminders.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. Problem Statement</h2>
        <p>
            Many patients miss their medication doses due to forgetfulness, busy schedules,
            or lack of proper organization. Some existing solutions are complex or require
            constant internet access, making them unsuitable for all users.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. Objectives of the Project</h2>

        <h3>Main Objective</h3>
        <p>
            To develop a mobile application that reminds users to take their medication
            at the correct time.
        </p>

        <h3>Specific Objectives</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Allow users to add and manage medicine details</li>
            <li>Enable users to schedule reminder times</li>
            <li>Send notifications when it is time to take medicine</li>
            <li>Track taken and missed doses</li>
            <li>Ensure the application works offline</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Scope of the Project</h2>
        <p>The project includes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>An Android application developed using Kotlin</li>
            <li>Local storage of medication data</li>
            <li>Reminder notifications</li>
            <li>Basic medication history tracking</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The project does not include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Online database synchronization</li>
            <li>Integration with healthcare providers</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>5. System Overview</h2>
        <p>
            The system consists of a user interface for managing medicines and reminders,
            reminder scheduling logic, and local data storage to save medication details
            and history.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Functional Requirements</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>The system shall allow users to add, edit, and delete medicines</li>
            <li>The system shall allow users to set reminder times</li>
            <li>The system shall send notification alerts</li>
            <li>The system shall allow users to mark medicines as taken or missed</li>
            <li>The system shall store data locally</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Non-Functional Requirements</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>The application should be easy to use</li>
            <li>Notifications should be reliable and timely</li>
            <li>The application should function without internet access</li>
            <li>User data should be stored securely on the device</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
            The medication reminder mobile application aims to help users manage their
            medication effectively through reminders and basic tracking. The system
            focuses on simplicity, reliability, and offline functionality to support
            better medication adherence.
        </p>
    </div>

</body>
